caption: b'"I was flying over the Malacca Strait when I saw this isolated lightning cloud and started continuously shooting photos and videos. I got lucky with this one amazing bolt, which I felt resembled a giant question mark in the sky.\xe2\x80\x9d \n#ShotoniPhone by Sam J. @samjsn'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI started this series as a way to stay creative and document my surroundings during quarantine. But these photos represent so much more than the virus. These simple pieces of plastic, cloth, and paper are a reminder of the loss, the hardship, the political divide, and the strangeness that has overtaken our lives in 2020. It\xe2\x80\x99s a historical time stamp.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Trevor T. @trevortraynor'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cIn my hometown Porto, wildlife and urban life coexist on a daily basis, and capturing these animals is an exercise of extreme patience and perseverance. I have to gain their confidence, watch their behavior, foresee their next move. Sometimes it takes a long time to take one nice shot.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Diogo L. @diogolage'
b'#iPhone12ProMax Night mode landscapes. Lowlight is no longer the enemy. \n#ShotoniPhone by Cody C. @codycobb'

b'Commissioned by Apple. Learn how to create amazing Night mode stills and Time-lapse videos with glow-sticks + string lights + a tripod + the #iPhone12.

Night mode Time-lapse lets you turn the dark into your own personal creative canvas. All you need is the #iPhone12, a tripod (or something steady to prop it on) and something bright. 

Skipping with string-lights creates beautiful long streaks. Attaching glow-sticks to a (non-glow) stick lets you paint with color. Or, you can just wave them over someone (gently) to give them a beautiful glow. 

If you don\xe2\x80\x99t have these, anything that emits light will do - like a flashlight or even another iPhone.

Remember, the key to a good Night mode Time-lapse video is keeping the subject matter as still as possible, whilst keeping the light source moving smoothly and consistently.

Try it tonight! 

#ShotoniPhone 12 by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign

Music: \xe2\x80\x9cOverflow\xe2\x80\x9d by @itsmdnt'

b'Commissioned by Apple. Learn how to shoot psychedelic liquid formations with water + food coloring + baby oil + Dolby Vision on the #iPhone12.

The small size of the #iPhone12 lets you get up close to things other cameras can\xe2\x80\x99t. 

Fill a clear container half way up with water, add a few drops of food coloring and fill the rest with baby oil - remember to close the lid tightly!

With the camera open, position the iPhone 12 right up to the jar, and tap and hold the screen to initiate focus-lock at the point the oil and water meet. This keeps everything nice and sharp.

Now it\xe2\x80\x99s time to shake shake shake. Or slowly tumble. Or even just let it sit. Different moments create different effects. Do it against some bright colorful paper for extra pop.

Try it today and see the world from a different perspective, or stay tuned for our last Everyday Experiment.

#ShotoniPhone 12 by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign 

Music: \xe2\x80\x9cImpression\xe2\x80\x9d by @luciantune'

b'Commissioned by Apple. Learn how to create mesmerizing, squishy loops with balloons + water + colorful paper + Slo-mo on the #iPhone12.

With a tripod (or a friend who can hold very still), position the iPhone 12 over some colorful paper, select Slo-mo and start bouncing. Regular balloons work best because they won\xe2\x80\x99t burst as easily.

After you\xe2\x80\x99ve got some great shots, you can adjust the Slo-mo timing by tapping edit and moving the slider to capture the exact moment the balloon hits the card.

Lastly, if you want to get suuuuper fancy, bring the footage into iMovie on your iPhone and use the green-screen effect (it works on any color) to layer multiple clips over each other. Cool, huh?

Try it today (if it\xe2\x80\x99s nice out) or stay tuned for more Everyday Experiments.

#ShotoniPhone 12 by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign

Music: \xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s a Game\xe2\x80\x9d by Show Pony'

b'One beautiful photo, two beautiful memories.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cOne afternoon in August, after a long period of social distancing, we\xe2\x80\x99re on a family vacation when the sun goes down and perfectly lights my niece and nephew\xe2\x80\x99s faces. This is a portrait of their beautiful innocence, and a reminder of a peaceful moment in these difficult times.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Matteo F. @thelittlebean'

b"Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cWhen I create, whether it's the masks themselves or the photos of them, I don\xe2\x80\x99t try to think too much. For the masks, colors and textures are important to me. For the photos, all I really care about is the light. The rest is play.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Magnhild K. @damselfrau"

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI was walking down the streets of Paris one morning when I found this reflection of the sunrise on a puddle. The sun seems to embrace the building. It\xe2\x80\x99s the beginning of a great day." #ShotoniPhone by Guillaume L. @guillaumelavrut'

b'Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cUsing only the light + liquid from a glow stick and the #iPhone12Pro we re-created a primordial ocean, teaming with early life.\xe2\x80\x9d

\xe2\x80\x9cNext, we used a piston to fire rocks past an #iPhone12Pro in free fall.\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0Slo-mo + the amazing lens stabilization made it seem like we\xe2\x80\x99re flying through an asteroid field in deep space. Cool, huh?\xe2\x80\x9d

\xe2\x80\x9cLastly, by using a simple object I can obscure a light to create an eclipse.\xe2\x80\x9d

It\xe2\x80\x99s all a matter of perspective in Experiments V: Dark Universe. Watch the full film on IGTV or head to YouTube for a look behind the scenes and see how it was made.

#ShotoniPhone 12 Pro by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign'

b'Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cHow do we show energy itself? We thought about plasma tubes. When you shoot it at 4K, it looks like neurons firing.\xe2\x80\x9d 

\xe2\x80\x9cNext: a fish tank, a paint-filled balloon, and the new #iPhone12Pro = The Cloud Tank. With the new low-light capabilities, we were able to capture a balloon popping underwater, creating the impression of a nebula forming.\xe2\x80\x9d

Watch Experiments V: Dark Universe on IGTV or head to YouTube for a look behind the scenes and see how it was made. 

#ShotoniPhone 12 Pro by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign'

b'How we capture something is often just as important as what we capture. \n\n\xe2\x80\x9cHaving my camera in my pocket makes it much easier to capture a singular moment. I\xe2\x80\x99m always ready when I find a beautiful reality, like this texture of red rocks or any of the breathtaking scenery. With my framing, I\xe2\x80\x99m trying to go beyond that reality as much as I can, to see things out of the box." #ShotoniPhone by Benjamin C. @benjamincolombel'

b'No detail is too small.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cThe colors were chosen in coordination with the location for the shoot. I wanted something that would match the subject and standout in the overall frame as well, with the blue sky and surrounding cliff aesthetic as a backdrop. It\xe2\x80\x99s meant to capture where earth, sea and endless sky meet.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Joseph A.M. @sarf_bort'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI was on a study visit at the zoo with a group of students. At first glance, there was nothing about the deer that caught my eye. But after a few minutes of watching, they started to look like they were sprayed with white dots." #ShotoniPhone by Nasil N. @nasil_nazer'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI am lost in thought as I look out at the endless horizon. The clear, brilliant blue color of the sea relaxes the mind. Everything nature creates lives in harmony." #ShotoniPhone by Eunseol J. @seolarchive'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cPhotography creates an exclusive space that belongs to me and my subject, undisturbed by the mundane world. I walk around at will, keeping an ideal distance from everything that is happening, and the moment I decide to press that little button, I complete my one-way interpretation of every work in that space." #ShotoniPhone by Tessa C. @tautoism'

b'Do you walk your dog? Or does your dog walk you?

\xe2\x80\x9cMy dog is not interested in plodding along next to anybody. She is a force of nature. Everything she does is worth trying to capture, even if she\xe2\x80\x99s a blur going past most of the time."
#ShotoniPhone by Ann H. @alice1280'

b'Color conveys emotion.

\xe2\x80\x9cIn our culture, these vibrant colors are linked to festive moments like weddings, naming ceremonies, birthdays and festivals. They are associated with pure joy. I decided to celebrate my mom in the traditional African colors for all she has done for me."
#ShotoniPhone by Horace M. @yung_horace'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99m always watching how colors come in and out of frame, and how certain colors play off one another. These elements allow me to see the story going on within the scene. A lot of them are simple, ordinary and unlikely, but to me, it\xe2\x80\x99s those mundane moments that draw me in closer.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Joe G. @ioestreet'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cAs a fan of old horror movies and the history of the Arctic exploration, I mix these two passions into my vision. I try to visualize and hyperbolize impressions of the first Arctic explorers in front of greatness and the threat of the untouched Arctic nature while I\xe2\x80\x99m shooting.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Denis B. @astromadman'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cYou could hear the wind blow through this paddy field. It was relaxing to hear the birds chirping and frogs croaking, an entirely different environment than I\'m used to in the city." #ShotoniPhone by Muhammad F. @farisofar'

b'On National Public Lands Day, we are reminded of our role to preserve the natural world around us. \n\n\xe2\x80\x9cWhen humans love something, we protect it. That is deeply coded in all of our DNA. When we fall in love with any part of the natural world, we will go to great lengths to protect it. One of the best ways to nurture the world and all that lives in it, then, is to help others find something to love there. That is one of my duties: to tell visual stories that, at their best, help people find love for the natural world in which we all exist.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Anson F. @ansonfogel'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThe atmosphere created at sunset on these beaches is unique, with light partially cut by the cliffs. We take advantage of every moment to play. It also brings back memories of my courtship with my wife, mother of my two daughters, with whom I now share these sunsets.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Paulo T. @pajo7780'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI wanted to capture a moment with my horse, Sirena, to show the contrast between her ginger tone and the grass she was walking through. You can see the changing of the season from a dry winter to a green spring.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Mariana N. @mnarvaezdlp'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99ve always had an interest in nature since childhood. All I lacked was someone who could help me understand how to capture wildlife. For me, my brother was my first tutor and helped me understand how to make better compositions.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Arun C.R.D. @anecdotesbyarunchandra'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cColor is a tool for expressing emotions, a tool to speak more honestly about the feelings of the day. I like taking pictures in time and space where I can express colors well. I have a fairy-tale moment every day at sunset.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Chaewoo R. @ryufill_foto'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI rely a lot on my instincts. I rely on the sensations I feel in a given moment, on what the place suggests to me, or on the energy I feel in someone\xe2\x80\x99s face. With a series like this, initially everything is so chaotic, but then I realize there is almost always a through line that connects those images.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Leandro C. @leandrocolantoni'

b'Shot and Edited on iPhone, commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cMy work is all about continuing the legacy of the rainbow pride flag. By taking this symbol and applying it to the physical world, I want to reimagine the world as a queer-normative space, one that honors the full spectrum of gender and sexual diversity.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotandEditedoniPhone by Ramzy M. @space.ram'

b'Shot and Edited on iPhone, commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cCreating this work was originally a way for me to escape real life and build my own universe, sometimes loud and psychedelic and other times more pastel and moody. They are all actual photographs, capturing real places and structures. I am literally just placing a filter over reality\xe2\x80\x94which in a sense makes me more grounded and appreciative of everything I have and am able to do in this life on Earth.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotandEditedoniPhone by Mischelle M. @lilmisch'

b'Shot and Edited on iPhone, commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cColors are not only mesmerizing and beautiful, but they have the ability to evoke feelings and communicate intentions. You must explore, experiment and be creative with the immediate elements at your disposal.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotandEditedoniPhone by Rapheal O. @afrocheampong'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cBefore I took this image, I knew it needed to be black and white. The bright, overcast skies complimented the dark foreground grass, splitting the image in two. The white horse stood out perfectly against the foreground, an excellent subject.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by John K. @johnkrausphotos'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI sometimes take my friend\xe2\x80\x99s son, Maxime, for walks to a park or playground. I was showing him the shadows on the wall by making different figures and creatures with my fingers when I noticed this moment and captured it.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Sveta S. @strugatskaya'

b'Timing is everything.

Emanuele waited for the perfect moment to capture the moon floating above Bisentina Island.

\xe2\x80\x9cOn July 8th, early in the morning, I went to the garden. I waited until 6:19AM, when the moon was perfectly aligned with the island of the lake. Nature gives something extraordinary every day. Look, and treasure it every time.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Emanuele P. @onorevole_2012'

b'After admiring the beauty of this playful creature, take a minute to learn something new about its home.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cThe tropical rainforest in southern Costa Rica is considered the most biologically intense place on earth. My projects aim to motivate people to care about nature and wildlife conservation.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Tico H. @ticoswildstudio'

b'Inspiration comes in many forms.

Coming out of a difficult 2 years of his life, Nana transformed his insights into art.

\xe2\x80\x9cI connect with my subjects by virtue of race, ethnicity, or shared experiences living in the same geographical area. Portraits help communicate the subject\xe2\x80\x99s emotions without saying a word and bring out their physical identity.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Nana A. @as0mani'

b'Share your body\xe2\x80\x99s story.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cI hope people are able to recognize how much of the earth is in us, how connected we still are to it. I hope they can recognize the patterns in human bodies and see the similar patterns that exist in nature. I hope they learn to normalize scars and with time, see our bodies not as sites of trauma, but rather as monuments of healing.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Yagazie E. @yagazieemezi'

b'In every photo lies a life lesson. That is, if you take the time to stop and admire\xe2\x80\xa6

\xe2\x80\x9cSometimes you need to stop moving in the same direction every day, without thinking.

Sometimes it is necessary to take time from the tension of the day and look at the color of the setting sun; say goodbye to the fatigue of the day with the sun.

Stand in front of the historical place you went to see the past and learn from it, and fall silent.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Rizvan B. @rizvan.bagirli'

b"The gentle side of masculinity.

This photographer aims to depict brotherhood and male affection that is rarely seen in a culture that is typically painted as hyper-masculine.

\xe2\x80\x9cThe images are there to showcase beauty. There is a general theme 'Celebrating Us', and it says a lot about brotherhood or male companionship, but no deeper story behind it.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Justin Andy A. @mensahshot"

b'A gentle reminder to stop, and seek art.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cI focus on natural light, and how very ordinary moments can be made extraordinary through photos. I\xe2\x80\x99m not looking for very special or rare moments. The beauty is in everyday life.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Bhoopendra M. @bhupendra_1204'
b'Damien Chazelle shows us how to turn vertical videos into #VerticalCinema #ShotoniPhone. Watch now on IGTV.'

b'Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cWe started with this basic idea that everything was going to be shot vertically. And then that helped dictate what we were going to shoot and what kind of story we were going to tell.\xe2\x80\x9d #VerticalCinema #ShotoniPhone and directed by Damien Chazelle'

b'Look at your child and imagine the person they will grow to be.

Angela, a mother, looks down at her child and notices the magic in his freckles and lashes.

\xe2\x80\x9cI always, always hope that when others see my work of my son, they see the love and connection we share. He is an old soul with a beautiful heart, and he just inspires me to keep capturing that.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Angela D. @angela.doran'

b'Imagine the meals we could share here.

It is easy to be consumed by the fear and negative emotions swirling our lives in 2020, but take a minute to appreciate the little things that life can give.

\xe2\x80\x9cI hope people enjoy the color and sense of serendipity of this scene, the coincidental match up of this moment. I was visiting family, and we got up early to take the dog on a walk in a small cove. It was a very foggy day, and I noticed the strange arrangement of the bright red chairs against the blueish fog rolling in from the sea. Classic British summer weather.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Josh E. @spicy.meatball'

b'Poetry in the streets of Los Angeles.

In the face of both a pandemic and a civil rights movement, street photographer Chloe Pang has used her artistry to tell her own story.

\xe2\x80\x9cWelcome to our utterly strange world! I\xe2\x80\x99ve been documenting life amidst this absurd double pandemic of COVID-19 and racism. Social distancing hasn\xe2\x80\x99t changed the way I interact with my subjects, but the pandemic has changed the way people react to my presence. Being Korean-American, there\xe2\x80\x99s been a palpable, omnipresent tension due to a rise in xenophobia. When the Black Lives Matter protests began, the reemergence of community morale gave me a sense of security [in public space] I hadn\xe2\x80\x99t felt since before quarantine.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone by Chloe P. @chloecpang'

-
2 + 4. Matt G. @mattgrubb.americas.waffle \xe2\x80\x9cCelebration this year will look markedly different, as it should.\xe2\x80\x9d
-
3 + 7. Devyn G. @devyngalindo \xe2\x80\x9cTo me, pride is as much about resistance as it is a celebration in the face of erasure.\xe2\x80\x9d

b'Commissioned by Apple. "I try to find objects with a similar theme, whether they are items from the same room or tell a story of an event that just happened\xe2\x80\x94like lunch. My inspiration often comes from the refrigerator. While at home, seeing the same objects over and over began to generate some new thoughts of what might stack nicely.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone this month #atHome by Scottie C. @scottie_cameron'

b'Community Brief 30: Pets
They may not be not human, but they\xe2\x80\x99re definitely family. 
Tag #ThePetsSeries + #ShotoniPhone 
We\xe2\x80\x99ll post favorites next week.
Music: \xe2\x80\x9cS\xc3\xbcp\xc3\xbcrgesi Yoncadan\xe2\x80\x9d by @altingunband'

b"Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cCooking during quarantine means getting creative with what we have. My four-year-old likes to move different pieces of food around to change the expressions on the faces \xe2\x80\x94 'He is happy! This one\xe2\x80\x99s sad. See, now he looks worried.' These days we carry all of these feelings inside. I remind the boys (and myself) it\xe2\x80\x99s okay to hold many different emotions at once.\xe2\x80\x9d #ShotoniPhone last week #atHome by Erin J. @theindigobunting"

b'Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cThe situation we\xe2\x80\x99re all living has my mind working in so many ways to avoid boredom and anxiety. Getting away from home has always been my way of dealing with these things and expressing my creativity, but now being in lockdown has made me more aware of my immediate opportunities and advantages. I moved to this apartment less than a month ago, so this place symbolizes a new stage in my life. It\xe2\x80\x99s very special to me. It has light coming in all day long because of the positioning of the building, sometimes even too much. Being so close to the equator, though, our \'magic hour\' is very short, so I have to wait for it and be aware of the time. It\xe2\x80\x99s like a hunt for light." #ShotoniPhone last month #atHome by Juan B. @juan_brenner'

b'Commissioned by Apple. \xe2\x80\x9cI don\xe2\x80\x99t want to give up on life right now. My entire state of mind revolves around that fact with everything going on. So I wake up everyday with specific activities in my house to keep me going, starting with photography, working out, and a lot of dancing. It\xe2\x80\x99s been my daily routine. I\xe2\x80\x99m honestly still not used to shooting at home this much, or photographing myself for that matter. But I\xe2\x80\x99ve come to love the idea of capturing what my daily activities look like. b'Everything feels different now. It\xe2\x80\x99s unclear how long this will last, or what life will look like when it\xe2\x80\x99s all behind us. And while much is uncertain, some inspiring things are happening, too. All over the world, we\xe2\x80\x99ve seen an outpouring of creativity in the face of this crisis.
